External knowledge to enhance clarity:
- Published content refers to content where `is_published` equals 1;
- Average star rating is the mean value of all ratings a piece of content has received, with ratings presumably being on a 1-5 scale.

- Engagement score is a measure of how well content performs, typically based on the number of views, shares, comments, and ratings it receives; 
- A higher engagement score indicates more engagement, and thus, more successful content; 
- The query considers the top 10 content pieces per publisher to provide a comprehensive view of successful content across different publishers.
